    &lt;Title&gt;Unhelpful receptionist&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended A&amp;amp;E after having an injury. My only complaint was my first contact at the reception. I was in a wheelchair due to the injury so therefore lower than the reception desk. The 2 receptionist did not acknowledge that myself and my Husband were there and eventually one of them lifted their head and said “are you all right”? Possibly the most inappropriate question to ask someone standing in an A&amp;amp;E reception. She asked me my details and it was hard to hear her being so low down and I told her I was having difficulty hearing her but it made no difference. I work in a reception role myself for the NHS and I was dumbfounded by the lack of their communication skills and their customer service skills.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
